                  <decoDesc>
                  <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d1">
                  Decorative designs:
                  multiple full stops are used as section dividers throughout;
                  <locus target="#121r #150v #151r" facs="123 153">fols. 121r, 150v, 151r</locus> (multiple full stops connected by alternating red and black dots)
                  </decoNote>
                </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                  <list>
                    <item xml:id="e1">
                    <locus target="#ir(ecto) #iv(erso) #iir(ecto) #iiv(erso) #151v #152r #152v" facs="001 002 003 154 155">Fols. ir(ecto), iv(erso), iir(ecto), iiv(erso), 151v, 152r, 152v</locus>
                    <desc>
                    blank
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e2">
                    <locus target="#1r" facs="003">Fol. 1r</locus>
                    <desc>
                    The quire number “18” appears in the upper margin of the folio. Volume 1 (EMIP 655) contains 17 quires
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e3">
                    <desc>
                    A note in the andemta: “Here is the midpoint of the Faith of the Fathers, like the midpoint of Isaiah is “great slaughter in Edom” [Isaiah 34:6], like the midpoint of the Acts of the Apostles is “<foreign xml:lang="gez">እንተ አልባቲ ዘይገሃግሃ</foreign>” [Acts “there is no one in her who disputes”]; like the midpoint of the Epistles of Paul is “Oh, foolish Galatians!” [Galatians 3:1].”
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e4">
                    <desc>
                    Numbered quires: quires 18–32
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e5">
                    <locus target="#35v #44v #65r #76v" facs="038 047 067 079">Fols. 35v, 44v, 65r, 76v</locus>
                    <desc>
                    words of text are written interlinearly;
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e6">
                    <locus target="#21v" facs="024"> f. 21v, col. 2, line 18</locus>
                    <desc>
                    words of text are written in the upper margin with a symbol (+) marking the location where the text is to be inserted (21v);
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e7">
                    <locus target="#18r #105v #140v" facs="020 108 143">Fols. 18r, 105v, 140v</locus>
                    <desc>
                    text has been removed
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                  </list>
